def: Flattened or depressed at the poles; as, the earth is an oblatespheroid.
A babe or young child of Indian parentage in North America.
Lit., closed sea; hence, a body of water within the separatejurisdiction of the nation; -- opposed to open sea, the water open toall nations and over which no single nation has special control.
Having a peduncle; supported on a peduncle; pedunculate.
Of or pertaining to the psychrometer or psychrometry.
Having a tendency to flow in; having influence; influential.[R.] Holdsworth.
A folding or fold; a plait. Richardson.
Of or pertaining to Saturn, whose age or reign, from themildness and wisdom of his government, is called the golden age.
